    <div class="container-fluid bg-primary text-white p-3 mb-4">
        <h1 class="text-center">Bootstrap Container Examples</h1>
    </div>

    <!-- Default Responsive Container -->
    <div class="container container-section">
        <h3>.container (Responsive Fixed-Width)</h3>
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-md-6">Column 1 (md-6)</div>
            <div class="col-md-6">Column 2 (md-6)</div>
        </div>
        <p>This container has a fixed maximum width that changes at different breakpoints (sm, md, lg, xl, xxl). It's centered on the page.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Fluid Container -->
    <div class="container-fluid container-section">
        <h3>.container-fluid (Full Width)</h3>
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-sm-4">Column 1 (sm-4)</div>
            <div class="col-sm-4">Column 2 (sm-4)</div>
            <div class="col-sm-4">Column 3 (sm-4)</div>
        </div>
        <p>This container always spans the entire width of the viewport, regardless of the screen size.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Responsive Container until Small Breakpoint -->
    <div class="container-sm container-section">
        <h3>.container-sm (100% until sm, then fixed)</h3>
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-lg-3">Column 1 (lg-3)</div>
            <div class="col-lg-3">Column 2 (lg-3)</div>
            <div class="col-lg-3">Column 3 (lg-3)</div>
            <div class="col-lg-3">Column 4 (lg-3)</div>
        </div>
        <p>This container is 100% wide until the small (sm) breakpoint, after which it behaves like a standard fixed-width container.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Responsive Container until Medium Breakpoint -->
    <div class="container-md container-section">
        <h3>.container-md (100% until md, then fixed)</h3>
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-xl-4">Column 1 (xl-4)</div>
            <div class="col-xl-4">Column 2 (xl-4)</div>
            <div class="col-xl-4">Column 3 (xl-4)</div>
        </div>
        <p>This container is 100% wide until the medium (md) breakpoint, then it becomes a fixed-width container.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Responsive Container until Large Breakpoint -->
    <div class="container-lg container-section">
        <h3>.container-lg (100% until lg, then fixed)</h3>
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-xxl-6">Column 1 (xxl-6)</div>
            <div class="col-xxl-6">Column 2 (xxl-6)</div>
        </div>
        <p>This container is 100% wide until the large (lg) breakpoint, after which it adopts a fixed width.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Bootstrap JS (optional, for components like dropdowns, etc.) -->
    <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.3/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js"></script>
